@emph{The most frequently encountered problem with
voltage-signalling UPSes (e.g. BackUPS 650) is that you have
incorrectly specified which cable is being used.} All cables
furnished by APC have the cable number stamped on the side of the
computer connector end of the cable. Using this number with
apcupsd will normally work fine. If you do
not know what cable you have, you can use the
apctest program to determine the type of
the cable.

For simple signaling UPSes, you should @emph{not}
use @strong{simple} in the cable specification
(i.e. @strong{UPSCABLE simple}) unless you
have made the cable yourself according to the wiring diagram given in
the cables chapter of this manual.

