@node Bizarre Intermittent Behavior, , , Once you have established serial communications
@subsection Bizarre Intermittent Behavior

In one case, a user reported that he received random incorrect
values from the UPS in the status output. It turned out that
gpm, the mouse control program for command
windows, was using the serial port without using the standard Unix
locking mechanism. As a consequence, both
apcupsd and gpm
were reading the serial port. Please ensure that if you are running
gpm that it is not configured with a serial
port mouse on the same serial port.

