@section Diagram for cable hackers

If you are handy with cable creation tools, check out the @uref{http://www.exploits.org/nut/library/940-0024C.jpg,940-0024C clone diagram}. That's the black "smart" cable
normally provided with APC models sold after 1996. The loopback pins
on that diagram are used to keep PowerChute happy by allowing cable
detection. If you use the @uref{http://www.exploits.org/nut/,NUT} apcsmart driver, those
pins don't matter.

Many thanks to Steve Draper for providing this scan.

